n \in \mathbb N
\displaystyle\frac{3^k}{k}
\frac{3^{2^n}}{2^n}
3^{2^{n-1}} \equiv 1 \pmod {2^n}
3^{2^{n-1}} = M2^n + 1 \implies 3^{2^n} = \left(3^{2^{n-1}} \right)^2 = \left(M2^n + 1 \right)^2 = 2^n \left( M^2 2^n + 2M\right) + 1
\dfrac{3^{2^n}}{2^n} = 2 M \left(2^{n-1} M + 1 \right) + \dfrac1{2^n}
